    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We engineered a machine learning approach, MSHub, to enable auto-deconvolution of gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) data. We then designed workflows to enable the community to store, process, share, annotate, compare and perform molecular networking of GC-MS data within the Global Natural Product Social (GNPS) Molecular Networking analysis platform.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes the MSHub auto-deconvolution and GNPS molecular networking pipeline for GC-MS data, and provides public datasets and reproducibility infrastructure (job retention, cloning, hyperlink sharing).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Can the auto-deconvolution and molecular networking pipeline described in the Nature Biotechnology 2020 manuscript be successfully re-run on the companion GC-MS dataset to reproduce the reported network and deconvolved spectra outputs?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We refer to the dataset spectral deconvolution tool within the GNPS environment as 'MSHub'.",
      "asbval:note": "MSHub is explicitly named and described as the auto-deconvolution tool integrated into GNPS.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "MSHub",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We deployed this functionality within GNPS/MassIVE (https://gnps.ucsd.edu). We refer to the dataset spectral deconvolution tool within the GNPS environment as 'MSHub'.",
      "asbval:note": "GNPS is the platform hosting MSHub and molecular networking workflows for GC-MS data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Once the summary file is generated by GNPS-MSHub or imported from another deconvolution tool, the spectra can be searched against public, private or commercial libraries. GNPS saves deconvoluted data as a summary file... Once the .mgf file is generated by GNPS-MSHub or imported from another deconvolution tool, the spectral features can be searched against public libraries.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes MGF file output from MSHub deconvolution containing deconvolved spectra.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Deconvolved spectra table (MGF or mzTab format) with individual compound mass-to-charge and intensity values",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One of the developments that enabled finding structural relationships within mass spectrometry data is spectral alignment, which forms the basis for molecular networking. GNPS has now expanded to include GC-MS-specific molecular networking. The output from GNPS can be exported for use in statistical analysis environments and for data visualization (e.g., Supplementary Figs. 7\u201310), including molecular cartography.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes molecular networking output and visualization capabilities but does not explicitly name GraphML, JSON, or PNG as output formats. The paper mentions export for visualization but specific file formats are not detailed in the provided passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Molecular network file and visualization (GraphML, JSON, or PNG) showing spectral clusters and cosine similarity edges",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Molecular networking can further guide the annotation at the family level by utilizing information from connected nodes rather than focusing on individual annotations. One can visualize aspects such as derivatized vs. non-derivatized, candidate compound class or subclass, instrument type or other metadata and inspect individual clusters of nodes.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes network analysis and visualization of clusters and nodes, but does not explicitly discuss 'network topology metrics' as a quantitative output. The focus is on visualization and annotation guidance rather than formal topology metrics.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Network topology metrics and comparison to reported network structure",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as a reproducibility/replication study ('Can the pipeline be successfully re-run'), which is consistent with the paper's emphasis on reproducibility and FAIR practices.",
        "The paper provides extensive infrastructure for reproducibility (job retention, hyperlink sharing, clone functionality, public datasets), supporting the feasibility of the proposed task.",
        "The card does not mention alternative deconvolution tools (MZmine/ADAP, MS-DIAL, etc.) that the paper explicitly supports as compatible inputs to GNPS, which could be relevant for a full reproduction workflow."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:11.441722+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
