    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstruct the MSHub auto-deconvolution module,' which could imply reverse-engineering or reimplementation. The paper describes MSHub as an existing tool deployed within GNPS, not as a task to be reconstructed by the user. The card may be conflating the paper's engineering of MSHub with a user-facing task.",
        "The research question is appropriately scoped to the paper's focus on auto-deconvolution methodology, but the card does not capture the paper's emphasis on scalability, reproducibility, and repository-scale operation as key innovations."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:30.751423+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_003/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "One of the developments that enabled finding structural relationships within mass spectrometry data is spectral alignment, which forms the basis for molecular networking. GNPS has now expanded to include GC-MS-specific molecular networking. ... Molecular networking can further guide the annotation at the family level by utilizing information from connected nodes rather than focusing on individual annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes that GNPS performs molecular networking on deconvolved GC-MS spectra and that networks are created through spectral similarity. However, the paper does not explicitly specify the output format (GraphML or JSON). The paper mentions exporting output for use in statistical analysis and visualization but does not name specific file formats for the network itself.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does the molecular networking step process deconvolved gas chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry spectra and what network output format does it produce?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:43.226627+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_003/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The GNPS leverages the repository infrastructure now has expanded to include GC-MS-specific deconvolution, reference spectra matching and molecular networking tools. ... GNPS/MassIVE lowers the expertise threshold required for analysis and encourages FAIR practices by promoting re-use of GC-MS data. ... The community infrastructure can be accessed at https://gnps.ucsd.edu under the header 'GC-MS EI Data Analysis'.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper refers to 'GNPS' with GC-MS-specific functionality and 'MSHub' as the deconvolution tool within GNPS, but does not use the exact name 'GNPS_GC'. The tool is accessed via GNPS at gnps.ucsd.edu under 'GC-MS EI Data Analysis'. The card names 'GNPS_GC' which appears to be a shorthand or alternate naming convention not explicitly used in the paper text.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS_GC",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:43.226627+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_003/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The output from GNPS can be exported for use in statistical analysis environments and for data visualization (e.g., Supplementary Figs. 7\u201310), including molecular cartography. ... The 3D model, feature table used for mapping and snapshots shown on the Figure 2f\u2013i are available at: https://github.com/aaksenov1/Human-volatilome-3D-mapping-. ... The GC-MS adapted MolNetEnhancer code with an example Jupyter notebook can be found here: https://github.com/madeleineernst/pyMolNetEnhancer.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms that GNPS outputs network data that can be exported for visualization and analysis, and mentions molecular networks are created through spectral similarity. However, the paper does not explicitly state that outputs are in GraphML or JSON format. The paper mentions exporting for visualization and statistical analysis but does not specify the network file format.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_003",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Molecular network file in GraphML or JSON format containing nodes (spectra/compounds) and edges (spectral similarity or MS/MS fragmentation matches)",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T05:59:43.226627+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_s41587_020_0700_3__task_003/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The card frames the task as 'reconstructing' the molecular networking module, which implies building or reimplementing it. The paper describes using the existing GNPS molecular networking functionality, not reconstructing it.",
        "The card's focus on 'network output format' (GraphML or JSON) is not explicitly addressed in the paper passages. The paper discusses network visualization and export for analysis but does not specify these particular file formats."
      ],
