    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "GNPS has now expanded to include GC-MS-specific molecular networking. One of the developments that enabled finding structural relationships within mass spectrometry data is spectral alignment, which forms the basis for molecular networking. In the case of EI, unlike in LC-MS/MS where the precursor ion mass is known, the molecular ion is often absent. For this reason, the molecular networks are created through spectral similarity of the deconvoluted fragmentation spectrum without considering the molecular ion. We explored molecular networking patterns for the EI data and observed that the EI-based cosine similarity networks are predominantly driven by structural similarity based on chemical class annotations.",
      "asbval:note": "Research question is well-supported by the paper's description of molecular networking via spectral similarity and cosine similarity-based network construction for GC-MS data.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Groups deconvolved gas chromatography\u2013mass spectrometry spectra by spectral similarity to identify and cluster chemically related compounds within complex mixtures. This enables structured molecular network assembly where nodes represent unique deconvolved spectra and edges refle",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:01:29.450863+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We deployed this functionality within GNPS/MassIVE (https://gnps.ucsd.edu). We refer to the dataset spectral deconvolution tool within the GNPS environment as 'MSHub'. GNPS has now expanded to include GC-MS-specific molecular networking.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper refers to the tool as 'MSHub' (the deconvolution engine) deployed within 'GNPS' or 'GNPS/MassIVE' environment. The card names 'GNPS_GC' which appears to be a GitHub repository reference (https://github.com/bittremieux/GNPS_GC mentioned in passage 6), but the primary tool name in the paper is 'MSHub' for deconvolution and 'GNPS' for the overall platform. The GitHub repository 'GNPS_GC' is mentioned for code availability but is not the primary tool name used in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "GNPS_GC",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:01:29.450863+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We engineered a machine learning approach, MSHub, to enable auto-deconvolution of gas chromatography-mass spectrometry (GC-MS) data. We then designed workflows to enable the community to store, process, share, annotate, compare and perform molecular networking of GC-MS data within the Global Natural Product Social (GNPS) Molecular Networking analysis platform. MSHub/GNPS performs auto-deconvolution of compound fragmentation patterns via unsupervised non-negative matrix factorization and quantifies the reproducibility of fragmentation patterns across samples. The tools are accessible through gnps.ucsd.edu.",
      "asbval:note": "The role description accurately captures the functionality: auto-deconvolution, molecular networking, spectral similarity computation via cosine similarity, and network topology output are all confirmed in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41587-020-0700-3",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "gc-ms-spectral-similarity-clustering",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools[0].role",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Web service and command-line interface for auto-deconvolution and cosine similarity-based molecular networking of GC-MS data; computes spectral similarity, clusters spectra, and outputs network topology.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:01:29.450863+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/mass-spectrum-extraction-and-formatting/000",
